 

The "skipStatus" property is a "getter" and a "setter" for the "skip" instance variable. It allows you to access and assign values to the "skip" variable from outside the "AiPlayer" class. 

  

The "turn()" method is the main method that controls the AI player's turn. He evaluates the last discarded card and tries to find a card in the player's hand that can be played. If the player does not have a playable card, he draws a card from the pile. 

  

The "addCards(Card other)" method adds a card to the player's hand. It is called when the player draws a card from the pile or receives a card from another player. 

  

The "turnEnd()" method is called at the end of the player's turn. He sends a message 
